Have taken out from here a few times, and until now it was a pretty good experience--tonight however was a different story and I absolutely will never be returning.  My girlfriend was about halfway through eating her soup when she encountered a soggy fly that was buried underneath a piece of tofu. We were both pretty disgusted and called the restaurant to inform them and ask for a refund. I threw out the soup, but made sure to take a photo so there was evidence. To our surprise, the man who answered the phone was not only unapologetic but outright rude. He immediately denied that there could have been a fly in our food, and claimed that unless we brought the soup with the fly in it to the restaurant, he wouldn't consider a refund--a photo apparently wasn't good enough evidence. When we protested that we shouldn't have to carry a dead fly several blocks to him to prove something that a photo showed just as well (in a politer tone than his, I might add), he hung up the phone!  Beyond the lack of hygiene suggested by our soup's unfortunate insect filling, I'm more upset at the fact that the restaurant refused to acknowledge the possibility that they made an error, and then jumped to the ridiculous accusation that we faked a photo of a dead fly to save $5. Easily the worst customer service experience I've had in recent memory.

I've been going to this place for nearly 26 years now. I usually get the dinner special #1 (Chicken w/ Broccoli) with white rice or their Chicken Lo Mein,  which is some of the best I've had in Baltimore. Not a big fan of their General Tso's Chicken and I'd skip their Chicken Rice Soup,  but the majority of the items on the menu are great. And be sure to grab a large lemonade or half & half,  which go  perfectly with any on the menu.
